Vestas Wind Systems A/S (VWS) , the worldâ€™s
largest wind turbine maker, has received an order to install 74
megawatts worth of turbines in South Africa.  The company, based in Aarhus, Denmark, plans to deliver 41
1.8-megawatt turbines in the fourth quarter of 2013, according
to a company statement today. Vestas did not disclose the
customer or the name of the project, which will be commissioned
by February 2014, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
